# 4.3 Project Root

The root folder contains the complete application.

It is responsible for:

- Project configuration
- Docker deployment
- Dependency management
- Git configuration
- Environment variables

Everything else is organized into subfolders.

---

# 4.4 app/

This is the heart of the application.

```
app/

server.py

agent.py

templates/
```

Responsibilities

- Flask application
- Google ADK
- Gemini
- MCP orchestration

---

# 4.5 server.py

server.py is the Flask application.

It is the entry point for all user interactions.

Responsibilities

- Starts Flask

- Serves HTML page

- Receives user questions

- Calls

```
run_query(question)
```

inside

```
agent.py
```

Returns

```
JSON Response
```

Example Flow

```
Browser

↓

POST /ask

↓

server.py

↓

run_query()

↓

agent.py
```

---

# 4.6 agent.py

This is the intelligence layer.

Everything related to AI exists here.

Responsibilities

- Load environment variables

- Create MCP Toolsets

- Configure Gemini

- Create ADK Runner

- Create Session

- Execute reasoning

- Receive tool outputs

- Return final response

It is the most important file in the project.

---

