# 4.18 Why This Folder Structure?

The organization follows software engineering best practices.

Benefits

✓ Clear separation of concerns

✓ Easier debugging

✓ Easier deployment

✓ Independent MCP servers

✓ Better maintainability

✓ Simpler onboarding

A new developer can immediately identify where

- UI lives

- AI logic lives

- MCP servers live

- Reports are generated

- Deployment is configured

without reading any code.

---

# 4.19 Key Takeaways

The Study Abroad Finder is intentionally organized into modular components.

Each file has a clearly defined responsibility.

This modularity made it possible to debug each MCP server independently, validate local and cloud deployments separately, and ultimately isolate the Filesystem MCP runtime issue that was resolved through Docker.

The folder structure therefore reflects not only the implementation, but also the architectural philosophy of the project:

> Keep reasoning, execution, presentation, deployment, and configuration independent wherever possible.